---
description: DEMA engineering rules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Product
DEMA modernizes a legacy customer/business workflow into a maintainable web platform.

# Stack
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite
- Backend: Python only
- Backend target: FastAPI, Pydantic v2, SQLAlchemy 2.0, Alembic, pytest, Ruff, Black
- Database target: PostgreSQL
- Current deployment: Vercel frontend + Render backend

# Working style
- Work milestone by milestone
- One branch per phase
- One primary agent per branch
- Keep the app runnable after each milestone
- Prefer small safe refactors over rewrites
- Preserve business behavior unless the current phase explicitly includes redesign
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies
- Update docs as part of implementation
- Add tests for risky logic

# Frontend rules
- No component should directly depend on localStorage or blob sync details once repository abstraction exists
- Separate UI, repository, mappers, validators, and hooks
- Separate record shape, form draft shape, and API DTO shape
- Split giant files by responsibility
- Avoid any

# Backend rules
- Keep route handlers thin
- Put business logic in services
- Put persistence logic in repositories
- Use Pydantic request/response schemas
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 style models
- Use Alembic migrations
- Add structured logging and central config

# Docs and quality
- Follow docs/operations/agent-playbook.md as the single source of truth
- Update weekly progress after meaningful milestones
- Run build/tests/smoke checks before considering a phase done
- If a milestone breaks smoke checks badly, revert and redo in smaller slices